<br>
One piece of advice for those of you who did not keep your skills up.  When you get that uber 2hb 50/43 weapon or whatever and your skill is 6 in 2hb....don't use that weapon to do your training.   Get yourself a cheap 2hb (applies for any of the skills) that's extremely fast, like a glowing wooden crook.   Use it whenever you're on an easy mob or you're not the main tank in your group, and your skill will go up a heck of a lot faster.<br>
<br>
I trained my fletching up to about 106 and stopped.  Once I could make the 150 range arrows to pull with, I figured I didn't need to get it up higher (will pay a real fletcher if I ever want a fletched bow.)   I carry my fletching kit always....serves as a backpack too.<br>
